CatDescriptText: Mrs. Thomas Lane, housewife, 2158 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?" Answer reads: "I feel that if some changes were made in both parties, conditions would be better."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Thomas Lane wearing eyeglasses, light colored button earrings, and short sleeved dress with floral eyelet and embroidered trim, standing on sidewalk, possibly Centre Avenue
